<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Editor. (Ed.). (Year of publication). <em>Title of book</em>. Place of publication: Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor">Smith, A.</span> (Ed.). 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Invertebrate taxonomy</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Parramatta, Australia</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Kowhai Press</span>.
</blockquote>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor">Smith, A., &amp;  Brown, B.</span> (Eds.). 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Sustainability in practice: Overcoming energy challenges in the 21st century</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Parramatta, Australia</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Northwoods Press</span>.
</blockquote>
