<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
If there is no author, use the editor&#8217;s name.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith (2056) indicates that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: Recent data (Smith, 2056) indicates that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the editor is referred to more than once in the same paragraph do not include the date in 
subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith (2056) indicates that&hellip; Smith also illustrates that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith (2056) observes that &#34;the ants had an advanced chemical defence system&#34; (p. 75).
	<br>
	Alternatively: In terms of sustainability, &#34;the ants had an advanced chemical defence system&#34; 
	(Smith, 2056, p. 75).
</blockquote>
